quarantine'''\n| Quarantine of town of '''[[Litovel]]''' and 18 nearby municipalities including '''[[Uni\u010dov]]''' and '''[[\u010cervenka (Olomouc District)|\u010cervenka]]'''.\n\nThe quarantine zone covers about 24,000 people. A cluster of 25 patients identified on 16 March 2020. By 21 March 2020 there were 54 confirmed patients within the quarantine zone out of 62 total confirmed cases in [[Olomouc region]].\n| 16 March 2020\n| From 16 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Lifted on 30 March 2020'''\n| People living and working within the quarantined area can go to work.\n\nPeople living within the area and working outside, and vice versa, must stay at home.\n\nWorkers returning from night shifts in the area to homes outside of the area ordered into 14 days' self-quarantine.\n\nPolice checkpoints on roads to the area. Only supply trucks, police, emergency, and fire rescue service can enter/leave town.\n\nMilitary field mini-hospital build in Litovel on 19 March.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor: Jakub Fajnor, tiskov\u00e9 odd\u011blen\u00ed MO |url=http://www.acr.army.cz/informacni-servis/covid/nasazeni-prislusniku-armady-cr-a-vojenske-policie-v-obci-litovel-220237/ |title=V Litovli na Olomoucku jsou ode dne\u0161ka nasazeni p\u0159\u00edslu\u0161n\u00edci Arm\u00e1dy \u010cR a Vojensk\u00e9 policie &#124; Ministerstvo obrany |publisher=Acr.army.cz |date=19 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n| Local health authority.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/olomouc/zpravy/koronavirus-unicov-litovel-cervenka.A200316_062222_olomouc-zpravy_jadv|title=Hygienici zav\u0159eli Litovel, Uni\u010dov a 19 obc\u00ed. V izolaci je 24 tis\u00edc lid\u00ed|date=16 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES}}</ref>\n|-\n| Quarantine of municipality of '''[[Kynice]]''', where a number of people were infected during the local volunteer fire department's ball.\n\nThe municipality has a population of 95.\n| 16 March 2020\n| From 16 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Lifted on 1 April 2020'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/kynice-izolace-konec-karanteny-koronavirus-hasici-dezinfekce_2004011116_tzr |title=Kynice opou\u0161t\u00ed po dvou t\u00fddnech karant\u00e9nu. V izolaci z\u016fst\u00e1vaj\u00ed pouze nemocn\u00ed, hasi\u010di \u010d\u00e1sti obce dezinfikuj\u00ed &#124; iROZHLAS \u2013 spolehliv\u00e9 zpr\u00e1vy |publisher=Irozhlas.cz |date=1 April 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n| Same conditions as in other quarantined areas.\n| Local health authority.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/hygienici-zcela-uzavreli-kynici-kde-se-virus-rozsiril-na-hasicske-zabave-40316848|title=Hygienici zcela uzav\u0159eli Kynice, kde se virus roz\u0161\u00ed\u0159il na hasi\u010dsk\u00e9 z\u00e1bav\u011b \u2013 Novinky.cz|website=novinky.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=8 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Social distancing measures'''\n| {{No|'''NATIONWIDE CURFEW'''}}\n| 15 March 2020\n| From 16 to 24 March 6&nbsp;am (Government Resolution)\n\nFrom 24 March 6&nbsp;am to 1 April 6&nbsp;am (Ministry of Health Protection Measure)\n\nExtended until 11 April.\n\nExtended until end of State of Emergency.\n| Order for persons to\n* a) limit their movement through public places as much as possible (with exemptions)\n* b) limit contact with others as much as possible\n\nExemptions:\n* a) reaching the workplace or profession\n* b) necessary visits to family or close persons\n* c) necessary travel for purchase of essentials (e.g. groceries, medicine, medical and hygiene supplies, pet food, etc.) including essentials for relatives and children, essential use of financial and post services, and personal vehicle refuelling.\n* d) necessary travel as mentioned in c) on behalf of another (e.g. neighbour, volunteer help)\n* e) travel to medical and social care facilities, including accompanying of another person for this purpose\n* f) travel to attend to urgent official matters, including accompanying of another person for this purpose\n* g) job performance (or attendant matters) in security, public health, individual spiritual service, public transport, and other infrastructure, citizen services (includes home deliveries)\n* h) movement in open countryside or parks\n* i) return travel to the place of residence\n* j) funerals\n\nScope of exemptions widened from 7 April onwards:\n* Conducting of sport activities at outside sporting grounds, in parks or in nature (e.g. tennis, skiing, sport shooting, etc.)\n** Facecover obligatory unless individuals conducting the given sport are at least 2 metres apart and\n** No more than 2 people are conducting sport together, with exception of members of the same household and with exception of staying 2 metres apart from others\n** Associated facilities (showers, changing rooms) remain closed / toilet can be open.\n\nScope of exemptions widened from 20 April onwards:\n* trainings of professional athletes (contact fighting sports not allowed, no spectators allowed)\n* marriage/resgistered partnership ceremony (official, newlyweds, 2 grooms + 4 persons allowed to attend)\n\nScope of exemptions widened from 27 April onwards:\n* church services attended by max 15 persons (under special arrangements - minimum distance of 2 meters between individuals, face masks, hand sanitizers, etc.). Churches may remain open for individual prayer / individual counselling.\n| Government Resolution No. 215/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"FreeMovementBan\">{{cite web|url=https://apps.odok.cz/attachment/-/down/IHOABMQVW63P |title=USNESEN\u00cdVL\u00c1DY \u010cESK\u00c9 REPUBLIKY |publisher=apps.odok.cz |year=2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12745/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"2 people ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40682&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20voln%C3%BD%20pohyb%20osob%20na%20%C3%BAzem%C3%AD%20%C4%8CR.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12745/2020-4/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"2 people ban 2\"/>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-4/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"sports allowed\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40882&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20omezen%C3%AD%20pohybu%20osob%20s%20v%C3%BDjimkami.pdf |title=Sports allowed |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-5/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"curfew 10 April\" />\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 16195/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40959&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20z%C3%A1kaz%20voln%C3%A9ho%20pohybu%20osob%20s%20v%C3%BDjimkami,%20s%20%C3%BA%C4%8Dinnost%C3%AD%20od%2020.%204.%202020.pdf |title=Data |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date=2020 |accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 16484/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40981&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20z%C3%A1kaz%20voln%C3%A9ho%20pohybu%20osob%20s%20v%C3%BDjimkami,%20s%20%C3%BA%C4%8Dinnost%C3%AD%20od%2027.%204.%202020.pdf |title=Data |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date=2020 |accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Public authorities' activity reduction'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| 14 March to 1 April.\n\nExtended until 11 April.\n\nExtended '''until 19 April'''.\n| '''Public authorities restricted to perform only to necessary duties.'''\n\nRestrictions on duties requiring personal contact with the public. Restriction of office hours to 3 hours on Monday and Wednesday. Only the lowest possible number of employees to be present when necessary. Duty to implement rotations of employees 