ration of making facemasks without sewing]]\n\nThe COVID-19 pandemic in the Czech Republic has created a wave of solidarity in a variety of areas, including:\n* Due to the lack of protective face-masks, volunteers sewed masks for other people and also shared instruction videos online.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor ave, kac zdroj: \u010cT24, Ministerstvo zdravotnictv\u00ed |url=https://ct24.ceskatelevize.cz/domaci/3063778-jak-si-vyrobit-nouzovou-rousku-bez-siti-socialni-site-radi-kus-latky-ministerstvo-i |title=Jak si vyrobit nouzovou rou\u0161ku bez \u0161it\u00ed? Soci\u00e1ln\u00ed s\u00edt\u011b rad\u00ed kus l\u00e1tky, ministerstvo i pap\u00edrov\u00fd kapesn\u00edk \u2014 \u010cT24 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ct24.ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Programmes were launched to help the most vulnerable groups and seniors, on a non-commercial basis, by buying food and medicines.<ref>{{cite web|author=Michal Burda |url=https://zlinsky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/pomoc-nejohrozenejsim-seniorum-privezou-nakupy-az-domu-20200318.html |title=Pomoc nejohro\u017een\u011bj\u0161\u00edm: senior\u016fm p\u0159ivezou n\u00e1kupy a\u017e dom\u016f \u2013 Zl\u00ednsk\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Zlinsky.denik.cz |date=18 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On Monday, 23 March, [[Czech Television|Czech National Television]] launched a temporary new television channel \u010cT3, which is to bring practical advice, news and a selection of \u010cT's classic programmes from the archive for older people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskatelevize.cz/porady/10000000408-naladte-se-na-ct3/ |title=Nala\u010fte se na \u010cT3 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* The Vietnamese community in the [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem]] region raised CZK 140,000 for a donation of a ventilator to a hospital in \u00dast\u00ed nad Labem<ref>{{cite web|author=Janni Vorl\u00ed\u010dek |url=https://ustecky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/vietnamska-komunita-se-slozila-na-plicni-ventilatory-pro-usteckou-nemocnici-20200323.html |title=Vietnamsk\u00e1 komunita se slo\u017eila na plicn\u00ed ventil\u00e1tory pro \u00fasteckou nemocnici \u2013 \u00dasteck\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Ustecky.denik.cz |date=23 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Due to the closure of Czech schools, Czech National Television launched an educational programme for home education. The \"U\u010d\u00edTelka\" programme is focusing on teaching first-grade pupils. The programmes \"Odpoledka\" on teaching second-grade pupils and programme \"\u0160kola doma\" for ninth grade pupils preparing them for entrance exams to secondary schools.<ref>{{cite web|author=16. 3. 2020, 10:52Jana Perglov\u00e1<!-- -->, Pr\u00e1vo |url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/ceska-televize-zacina-ucit-deti-zakladnich-skol-40316814 |title=\u010cesk\u00e1 televise za\u010d\u00edn\u00e1 u\u010dit d\u011bti z\u00e1kladn\u00edch \u0161kol |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Czech manufacturer of 3D printers [[Prusa Research]] contributed to the \"free use project\" of shared Bicycles company [[Rekola]] to enable access to transport with a lower risk of virus transmission than public transport.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/prusa-research-a-boj-s-koronavirem-jak-je-dulezite-byt-pripraven/ |title=Prusa Research a boj s koronavirem: jak je d\u016fle\u017eit\u00e9 b\u00fdt p\u0159ipraven \u2013 Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date=19 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> Prusa Research also designed, produced and distributed protective face shields for medical professionals.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/od-navrhu-k-hromadnemu-3d-tisku-zdravotnickych-stitu-behem-tri-dnu/ |title=Aktualizov\u00e1no 30.3. \u2013 Od n\u00e1vrhu k hromadn\u00e9mu 3D tisku zdravotnick\u00fdch \u0161t\u00edt\u016f b\u011bhem t\u0159\u00ed dn\u016f |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The \u017duf\u00e1nek family distillery from [[Bor\u0161ice]] will produce and distribute for free disinfectant gels without the necessary permit from the health and agriculture department.<ref>{{cite web | title=Zak\u00e1zali mi vyr\u00e1b\u011bt dezinfekci, st\u011b\u017euje si \u017duf\u00e1nek. O povolen\u00ed nest\u00e1l, \u0159\u00edkaj\u00ed celn\u00edci | website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz \u2013 V\u00edte, co se pr\u00e1v\u011b d\u011bje | date=23 March 2020 | url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/ekonomika/zufanek-dezinfekce/r~84235f126d0611ea80e60cc47ab5f122/ | language=cs | access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Empty_shelves_in_Tesco,_Skandin\u00e1vsk\u00e1,_Prague,_Czech_Republic,_during_COVID19_pandemic_(27_Feb_2020).jpg|Empty shelves of canned meat and other food in Tesco, Prague, on 27 February 2020\nFile:Let\u00e1k_MZCR_Coronavirus_A5.pdf|Information flyer from the Ministry of Health sent to every house address \nFile:Usnesen\u00ed vl\u00e1dy k vyhl\u00e1\u0161en\u00ed nouzov\u00e9ho stavu.pdf|Government Resolution on Declaration of Emergency\nFile:COVID-19_Czech_Government_SMS_notification_about_shop_shutdown.jpg|SMS notification of the closure of shops\nFile:Celetn\u00e1 ulice bez turist\u016f 2020 03 203.jpg|Prague, Celetn\u00e1 ulice, without tourists(March 2020)\nFile:Starom\u011bstsk\u00fd orloj bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|Prague, Astronomical clock, without spectators (March 2020)\nFile:V\u00e1clavsk\u00e9 n\u00e1m\u011bst\u00ed bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|thumb|Prague, Wenceslas Square, without tourists (March 2020)\nFile:Praha Flora karant\u00e9na b\u0159ezen 2020.jpg|Prague, Flora shopping centre (March 2020)\nFile:No entry to driver's area in Brno city transport due to COVID-19 (detail).jpg|Brno, forbidden to enter front section of local bus. (March 2020)\nFile:Westfield Chodov NCOV-19.jpg|Empty shopping mall in the Czech Republic during COVID-19 pandemic\nFile:Autobus, nevstupovat k \u0159idi\u010di (01).jpg|Interior of a Czech bus during COVID-19 pandemic (14 March 2020)\nFile:Antonov Airlines Antonov An-124-100 Vanzura-2.jpg|Antonov An-124-100 similar aeroplanetype which provided medical products purchased by the Czech government in China\nFile:Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9, drive-trhu COVID-19 testing.jpg|Drive thru testing centre at the University Hospital Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Healthcare in the Czech Republic]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/en/ COVID-19 epidemic (Ministry of Healthcare, in English)]\n* [https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19/ COVID-19 statistics (Ministry of Healthcare)]\n* [https://www.datawrapper.de/_/Sgf7v/ Epidemic curve in countries including the Czech Republic]\n* [https://covid-19-cz.chcepe.now.sh/ Interactive map of COVID-19 situation in the Czech Republic]\n* [https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://theenewstimes.com/corona-virus-live-statistics/ Live Statistics of Corona-virus on the World Map]\n\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Czech Republic|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Czech Republic|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic 