ciny-40312057|title=Government bans direct flights from China due to coronavirus|website=novinky.cz|access-date=3 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 4618/2020-2/MIN/KAN (revocation)<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40989&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20ochrann%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%203.%202.%202020%20k%20z%C3%A1kazu%20let%C5%AF%20z%20%C4%8C%C3%ADnsk%C3%A9%20lidov%C3%A9%20republiky.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of direct flights to/from selected regions of '''Italy'''.\n| 2 March 2020\n| From 5 March 2020 '''until 19 March 2020'''.\n| All direct flights to/from Italian regions Emillia-Romagna, Piemont, Lombardia, Venetia suspended.\n\nAround 100,000\u2013110,000 Czechs visited Northern Italy over the previous month (mostly for skiing holidays).\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-6/PRO<ref name=\"italy flights measure\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40428&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Ochrann%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20MZ%20%C4%8CR_lety%20It%C3%A1lie.pdf |title=Allie |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of direct flights to/from '''South Korea'''.\n| 2 March 2020\n| From 5 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Revoked on 24 March 2020.'''\n| All direct flights to/from South Korea suspended.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-5/PRO<ref name=\"Iran visas\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40429&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Ochrann%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20MZ%20%C4%8CR_lety%20Korea.pdf |title=Korea data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-15/PRO (revocation)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40697&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20ochrann%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%202.%20b%C5%99ezna%202020%20k%20z%C3%A1kazu%20let%C5%AF%20z%20Korejsk%C3%A9%20republiky.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of issuing of new visas in '''Iran'''.\n| 7 March 2020\n| From 7 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Revoked on 21 April 2020'''.\n| Applies to all applicants requesting visas in Iran (notwithstanding nationality).\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10384/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=visa.iran.stop>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/koronavirus-online-koronavir-cesko-nakazeni-ministr-vojtech-cina-chu-pej-wu-chan_2003070631_jgr|title=The Czech Republic has 5 new infections, total has grown to 26.|website=iRozhlas.cz|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10384/2020-2/MIN/KAN (revocation)<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40992&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%207.%203.%202020%20o%20zastaven%C3%AD%20p%C5%99%C3%ADjmu%20%C5%BE%C3%A1dost%C3%AD%20o%20v%C3%ADza%20v%20Teher%C3%A1nu.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| Random medical checks at major border crossings\n| 7 March 2020\n| From 9 March 7&nbsp;am onwards (indefinitely).\n| Major border crossings (Rozvadov, Folmava, \u017delezn\u00e1 ruda, Doln\u00ed Dvo\u0159i\u0161t\u011b, Str\u00e1\u017en\u00fd, Mikulov, Hat\u011b, B\u0159eclav, C\u00ednovec, and Pomez\u00ed) manned by a combination of police, customs, and fire service personnel.\n\nDrivers provided with informational leaflets in Czech, English, German and Italian.\n\nRandom temperature checks of vehicle occupants.\n\nSimilar measures put in place at all international airports as well as in cross-border trains.\n\nPeople with symptoms can either turn back at the border or be transported by a [[Dangerous goods|HAZMAT]] ambulance for medical examination at the nearest hospital.\n\nArmy deployed on 10 March (see below).\n| Government<ref name=\"border leaflets\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/ministerstvo-zdravotnictvi-vydalo-nove-mimoradne-opatreni-tykajici-se-karanteny-_18668_4107_1.html|title=Ministerstvo zdravotnictv\u00ed vydalo nov\u00e9 mimo\u0159\u00e1dn\u00e9 opat\u0159en\u00ed t\u00fdkaj\u00edc\u00ed se karant\u00e9ny osob, kter\u00e9 se vracej\u00ed z It\u00e1lie|website=mzcr.cz}}</ref><ref name=italy.quarantine.idnes>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/karantena-koronavirus-vyjimka.A200307_115240_domaci_zaz|title=The Czech Republic has 26 infected. Mandatory quarantine also for foreigners|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;\" | Restrictions on sale of medical means\n| '''FFP3 respirators sale ban'''\n\nFFP3 respirators may be sold only to:\n* healthcare providers (''exemption revoked on 6 March'')\n* welfare providers (''exemption revoked on 6 March'')\n* Czech Republic government and its component agencies\n* resellers of FFP3 based in the Czech Republic, provided resellers will sell only to the other groups mentioned\n| 3 March 2020\n| From 4 March onwards (indefinitely)\n\n'''Revoked on 6 April 2020'''\n| The FFP3 respirators sale ban was preceded by a memo from [[Security Information Service]] to the Government, according to which Chinese embassy in Prague was conducting massive purchases of respirators available on Czech market during January and February and transferring them to China.<ref name=\"BIS report\">{{cite web|url=https://denikn.cz/324728/cina-v-cesku-skupuje-respiratory-a-rousky-varovala-babise-a-ministry-bis/|title=\u010c\u00edna v \u010cesku skupuje respir\u00e1tory a rou\u0161ky, varovala Babi\u0161e a ministry BIS|last=Prchal|first=Luk\u00e1\u0161|date=24 March 2020|website=Den\u00edk N|language=cs|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThis led to shortage of FFP3 respirators for use by healthcare providers which lasted for weeks after the ban was passed.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-8/PRO<ref name=\"ffp3 sale restriction\">[[:File:Mimo\u0159\u00e1dn\u00e9 opat\u0159en\u00ed - z\u00e1kaz v\u00fdvozu v\u0161ech respir\u00e1tor\u016f t\u0159\u00eddy FFP3 mimo \u010cR.pdf]]</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-12/PRO<ref name=\"ffp3 sale restriction no 2\">{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/53/Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9_opat%C5%99en%C3%AD_-_prodej_osobn%C3%ADch_ochrann%C3%BDch_prost%C5%99edk%C5%AF_t%C5%99%C3%ADdy_FFP3.pdf |title=Prodej |publisher=upload.wikimedia.org |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40878&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%206.%203.%202020%20k%20prodeji%20OOP%20t%C5%99%C3%ADdy%20FFP3.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> (revocation)\n|-\n| '''Hand sanitizers export ban.'''\n| 5 March 2020\n| From 5 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Revoked on 21 April 2020'''.\n| Ban on export of hand sanitizers listed in Annex 1, Category 1 of EU Regulation No. 528/2012 (with exemption of small amounts for personal use).\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-9/PRO<ref name=\"hand sanitizers restrictions\">{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cf/Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9_opat%C5%99en%C3%AD_-_z%C3%A1kaz_v%C3%BDvozu_desinfekce_rukou.pdf |title=Aikaz |publisher=upload.wikimedia.org |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 16771/2020-2/MIN/KAN (revocation)<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40991&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%205.%203.%202020%20o%20z%C3%A1kazu%20v%C3%BDvozu%20desinfekce%20rukou.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| '''Ban on export of medication'''\n| 17 March 2020\n| From 17 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| 17 March \u2013 1 April 2020 \u2013 general ban on export of medication.\n\nFrom 1 April onwards \u2013 ban on export of selected medication.\n\nBan only on export of medication destined for the Czech market. Medication manufactured directly to foreign order may still be exported.\n| Government Regulation No. 104/2020 Coll. (until 1 April)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38815 |title=Sbirka |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment Regulation No. 146/2020. Coll (after 1 April)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38833 |title=Info |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Duty to report gatherings over 5,000 people.\n| Organisers must inform health authorities about all planned gatherings where they expect 5,000 or more visitors during a single day\n| 4 March 2020\n| From 4 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Revoked on 17 April'''\n| \n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 9826/2020-1/HES<ref name=\"gatherings 5000\">{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9_opat%C5%99en%C3%AD_-_nahl%C3%A1%C5%A1en%C3%AD_kon%C3%A1n%C3%AD_akc%C3%AD_nad_5000_osob.pdf |title=MIMO\u0158\u00c1DN\u00c9O PAT\u0158EN\u00cd |publisher=upload.wikimedia.org |year=2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 9826/2020-2/MIN/KAN (revocation)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40978&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%204.%203.%202020%20k%20hromadn%C3%BDm%20akc%C3%ADm%20nad%205000%20osob.pdf |title=Data |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date=2020 |accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|-\n<!--\n\nQ ---- U ---- A ----- R ----- A ----- N ----- T ----- I ----- N ------E\n\n-->\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=35 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Quarantine'''\n| Spectators banned from attending the World Biathlon Cup Championship race in [[Nov\u00e9 M\u011bsto na Morav\u011b]].\n| Championship can take place, but no spectators allowed.\n| 2 March 2020\n| From 5 March 2020 to 8 March 2020.\n|\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-7/PRO<ref name=\"Iran visas\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=4 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Residents returning from abroad ordered to self-quarantine for 14 days'''.\n| All residents of the Czech Republic (citizens and non-citizens), as well as other persons working in the Czech Republic who return to the country from '''Italy''', are ordered to contact their general practitioner by phone or email and self-quarantine for 14 days. Exemptions: (1) truck drivers that use FFP2 or FFP3 respirators while out of the vehicle in Italy, (2) ambulance crews under specific conditions and (3) pilots that did not leave their aeroplane while in Italy.\n| 7 March 2020\n| From 7 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\nReplaced by other measures (see below).\n\nFormally '''revoked on 17 April 2020'''.\n| Measure replaced a similar one that was issued a day earlier, which did not include any exemptions.\n\n'''Up to CZK 3 million fine for breach of self-quarantine.'''\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10381/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"border leaflets\"/>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10381/2020-2/MIN/KAN (revocation)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40979&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%207.%203.%202020%20k%20n%C3%A1vratu%20z%20pobytu%20na%20%C3%BAzem%C3%AD%20Italsk%C3%A9%20republiky.pdf |title=Data |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date=2020 |accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| Anyone who visited one of the '''selected countries''' over the past 14 days subject to mandatory self-quarantine of 14 days. List of countries may be updated daily.\n\n'''Anyone crossing borders into the Czech Republic must allow authorities to perform a medical check.'''\n| 10 March 2020\n| From 10 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Up to CZK 3 million (about EUR 120,000) fine for breach of self-quarantine.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10653/201-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"self-quarantine all travelers\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/cizincikteri-prekroci-hranice-crbudou-kontrolovani-na-priznaky-infekcniho-on_18703_4107_1.html|title=Cizinci, kte\u0159\u00ed p\u0159ekro\u010d\u00ed hranice \u010cR, budou kontrolov\u00e1ni na p\u0159\u00edznaky infek\u010dn\u00edho onemocn\u011bn\u00ed|website=mzcr.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n| All residents of the Czech Republic (citizens and non-citizens) who return from selected countries.\n\nList of selected countries subject to daily updates, as of the day of measure adoption they are: '''China, South Korea, Iran, Italy, Spain, Austria, Germany, Switzerland, Sweden, Norway, the Netherlands, Belgium, Great Britain, Denmark, and France'''.\n\nFreight drivers exempted and recommended to \"limit contact with locals as far as feasible\".\n| 13 March 2020\n| From 13 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\nReplaced from 14 April onwards.\n| Exemptions: \n* '''International freight transport''': drivers, flight crews, train crews, ship crews. Also exempt are freight transport workers employed abroad.\n* Diplomatic staff.\n* Emergency services while on duty (police, EMT, fire, mountain rescue, etc.).\n* Persons who verifiably periodically cross borders, especially workers with a place of employment no further than 100 kilometres from the border.\n* Citizens of Germany, Austria, Poland and Slovakia who verifiably periodically cross borders, especially workers with a place of employment no further than 100 kilometres from the border.\n* Epidemiology, humanitarian and health experts.\n* Members of the European Parliament.\n* Minors that are citizens of an EU Member state and whose parent is a Czech citizen.\n* Persons transporting blood, bone marrow and/or organs for purpose of transplantation.\n* Persons with a serious medical condition for purpose of undertaking medical procedures abroad.\n* Persons who merely used Airport Transit Zones within selected countries.\n\nUp to CZK 3 million (about EUR 120,000) fine for breach of self-quarantine.\n| Government Resolution No. 209/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"full on quarantine\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_209.pdf |title=Aktualne |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Interior Notice on Exemptions from travel restrictions during the State of Emergency<ref name=\"min interior notice on exemptions\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mvcr.cz/clanek/vyjimky-z-omezeni-cestovani.aspx|title=V\u00fdjimky z omezen\u00ed cestov\u00e1n\u00ed \u2013 Ministerstvo vnitra \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Anyone entering the Czech Republic has duty to contact health authority and may be subject to mandatory 14 days quarantine''' (with exemptions).\n| 6 April 2020\n| From 14 April until end of State of Emergency.\n| Exemptions \u2013 see referenced Government Resolution.\n\nSignificant change in rules from 27 April onwards - see border restrictions below.\n| Government Resolution No. 387 published as No. 150/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"third travel ban\" />\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 443 published as No. 193/2020 Coll. (revocation)<ref name=\"23 Apr Resolutions\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=4 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Contact tracing'''\n| {{No|'''Confirmed COVID-19 patients' contacts preventatively quarantined for 14 days.'''}}\n| 7 March 2020\n| From 8 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Authorities actively seek all people who were in contact with confirmed COVID-19 patients. \n\nThose are then ordered to mandatory 14 days' preventative self-quarantine. They also get tested for COVID-19, typically after 5 days.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10386/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"self quarantine-contacts\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/karantenu-pro-kontakty-nakazenych-osob-budou-nove-na-dalku-rozhodovat-prakticti-_18672_4107_1.html|title=Karant\u00e9nu pro kontakty naka\u017een\u00fdch osob budou nov\u011b na d\u00e1lku rozhodovat prakti\u010dt\u00ed l\u00e9ka\u0159i|website=mzcr.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Use of mobile phone geolocation data and debit card payments for contact tracing'''}}\n| 19 March 2020\n| From 19 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Mobile phone operators and banks obliged to provide geolocalisation data to health authority, if so requested. Data must be provided subject to following conditions (cumulative):\n* Only geolocation data of COVID19-positive person,\n* '''only subject to such person's explicit consent''' which may be taken back at any time,\n* geolocation data for previous three weeks,\n* data may be used only for purpose of epidemiologic tracing,\n* health authority may store the original data only for necessary period of time, no more than 6 hours.\n\nGeolocation data is used to draft a map of COVID19 person's movement in previous days. This map is then presented to the person to help them remember who they were in contact with, where and when. Identified contacts are then put into 14 days quarantine and tested for COVID19 after 5 days.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12398/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40616&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20na%C5%99%C3%ADzen%C3%AD%20pro%20oper%C3%A1tory%20ve%C5%99ejn%C3%BDch%20mobiln%C3%ADch%20komunika%C4%8Dn%C3%ADch%20s%C3%ADt%C3%AD%20a%20banky.pdf |title=Data |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n| Soldiers deployed to reinforce health authority.\n| 30 March 2020\n| From 30 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n| 300 soldiers (mainly paramedics and students of [[University of 