llet Beginning Story\" Elena Pavlova and Olga Sapphire Part 7 |url-status=live }}\n*{{cite web |ref={{harvid|\u95a2\u53e3|2009k}} |last1=\u95a2\u53e3 |first1=\u7d18\u4e00 |title=\u300c\u65e5\u672c\u306e\u30d0\u30ec\u30a8\u306f\u3058\u307e\u308a\u7269\u8a9e\u300d\u30a8\u30ea\u30a2\u30ca\u30fb\u30d1\u30f4\u30ed\u30d0\u3068\u30aa\u30ea\u30ac\u30fb\u30b5\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30a2\u3000\u305d\u306e\u5341\u4e00\u3000\u30a8\u30ea\u30a2\u30ca\u30fb\u30d1\u30f4\u30ed\u30d0\u3068\u8c9d\u8c37\u516b\u767e\u5b50 |url=https://www.chacott-jp.com/news/column/others/detail003777.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |website=Chacott.jp |publisher=Chacott Co., Ltd |date=31 January 2009 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200416192211/https://www.chacott-jp.com/news/column/others/detail003770.html |archivedate=16 April 2020 |location=Tokyo |language=Japanese |trans-title=\"Japanese Ballet Beginning Story\" Elena Pavlova, Olga Sapphire, and Yayoko Kaiya Part 11 |url-status=live }}\n*{{cite journal |ref={{harvid|''Ballet Today''|1970}}|title=Japan |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=af9xt7ib1mgC |journal=Ballet Today |volume=18 |issue=7\u201310 |location=London Ltd. |year=1970 |publisher=Newman Wolsey Limited |oclc=2521829}}\n*{{cite web |ref={{harvid|Japan Ballet Association|2016}}|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=\u65e5\u672c\u30d0\u30ec\u30a8\u754c\u306b\u5fd8\u308c\u3048\u306c\u8db3\u8de1\u3092\u5370\u3057\u305f\u4eba\u3005: \u5916\u56fd\u4eba\u7de8 |url=http://www.j-b-a.or.jp/o/ballet-people.html |website=\u516c\u76ca\u793e\u56e3\u6cd5\u4eba\u65e5\u672c\u30d0\u30ec\u30a8\u5354\u4f1a |publisher=Japan Ballet Association |date=2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160530123638/http://www.j-b-a.or.jp/o/ballet-people.html |archivedate=30 May 2016 |location=Tokyo |language=Japanese |trans-title=People Who Have Made Unforgettable Footprints in the Japanese Ballet World: Foreigners}}\n*{{cite book |ref={{harvid|\u65e5\u5916\u30a2\u30bd\u30b7\u30a8\u30fc\u30c4|2004}} |ti